game:the-witcher-2-assassins-of-kings-enhanced-edition a gf:Game ;
  gf:rawgId "NaN"^^xsd:integer ;
  gf:title "The Witcher 2: Assassins of Kings Enhanced Edition" ;
  gf:slug "the-witcher-2-assassins-of-kings-enhanced-edition" ;
  gf:releaseDate "2012-04-16"^^xsd:date ;
  gf:rating "4.17"^^xsd:decimal ;
  gf:metacriticScore "88"^^xsd:integer ;
  gf:playtime "7"^^xsd:integer ;
  gf:description "The player is Geralt of Rivia, infamous monster slayer. In the second game of the series, titular witcher is involved in the inner conflicts of Temeria, where he stopped the rebellion and was hired as a bodyguard of Temerian King Foltest. Eventually, Foltest was assassinated by a witcher-like assassin, and the only person fitting the description was Geralt. \nThe game combat system was reworked, in order to add traps and ranged throwing weapon, giving players more control over the course of the battle. It?s still a third person action RPG, and the player can upgrade and improve general abilities, swordsmanship, alchemy, and magic. \nThe enhanced edition includes additional hours of content, new cinematics, the original soundtrack, game manual and quest handbook, among other things. The new tutorial allows players to spend more time to master new game mechanics and see for themselves visual improvements to the core game." ;
  gf:imageUrl "https://media.rawg.io/media/games/6cd/6cd653e0aaef5ff8bbd295bf4bcb12eb.jpg"^^xsd:anyURI ;
